title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: In 2021, the UNICEF MCO Evaluation Function continued its efforts to support internal and external partners to understand, generate and use evaluation evidence for better programming and policy making. Results were built on three strategic pillars: ensuring high-quality evidence products via direct evaluation management; strengthening national capacities for using and conducting evaluations; and supporting the development of a National Evaluation System. The 6 evaluations, 2 trainings and 1 technical assistance conducted in 2021, in close collaboration with government and implementing partners, supported child responsive policy decisions, identification of pockets of inequalities and improved planning and investment for children.;; | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/01/2022
